    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>For javascript based debugging on eclipse, \"change value\" method and \"Max length\" method both failed for me, adding the required object to watch(<strong>Expressions</strong>) and then <strong>Right Clicking the watched expression to select \"Load Full Value\"</strong> is the only solution that works for me, but <strong>even this inserts unwanted \"\\n\" in the output</strong>. </p>\n\n<p><strong>Note</strong> - \"Max length\" must be set for the \"Load Full Value\" to work as it loads values till max length(default in eclipse is 10000). Refer above answer to see how to set Max length. </p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3648719,
      "reputation" : 39,
      "user_id" : 3041375,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/5ebbcb7112db4a500fabba33236a2671?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Sonali",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3041375/sonali"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1475578493,
    "creation_date" : 1475578493,
    "answer_id" : 39850440,
    "question_id" : 2873949,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>When debugger reaches the point where you want the String value, just type a sysOut statement</p>\n\n<pre><code>System.out.println(\"The value is : \\n \" + query);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Select the above the statement, <strong>right click-> Execute</strong></p>\n\n<p>It will print the value on the console</p>\n"
  }, {
