    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>The best way to view a String value from eclipse debug view is as below.</p>\n\n<p>1) Switch to debug view in Eclipse</p>\n\n<p>2) Select the desired variable in variable pane.</p>\n\n<p>3) Right click on display area of variable pane where value is shown and click on Max Length. Enter the maximum char value in Configure Details Pane .</p>\n\n<p>4) Cheers</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/EWS69.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/EWS69.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 5745825,
      "reputation" : 13081,
      "user_id" : 4537090,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 79,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/Dwxvn.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "WesternGun",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4537090/westerngun"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1492594676,
    "creation_date" : 1492594676,
    "answer_id" : 43491873,
    "question_id" : 2873949,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>There is no \"maxLength\" in Eclipse Mars. And, the \"change value\" only works with \"Variables\", not \"Expressions\", so none of above works for me. </p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/TwjCv.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/TwjCv.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n\n<p>And, the expression are cut in the middle, not at the end. I guess they changed the default behaviour.</p>\n\n<p>The only thing working for me, is to expand the expression name column's width, and click the expression to select it all to see the full length content.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4387361,
      "reputation" : 464,
      "user_id" : 3577053,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/794d404d577935358d185787fd56812a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "user07",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3577053/user07"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1584475977,
    "creation_date" : 1584475977,
    "answer_id" : 60729561,
    "question_id" : 2873949,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Nothing from the above worked for me, moreover, some user interface elements in my Eclipse can not be found as described. I'm using STS 4.3.1.</p>\n\n<p>The value I needed was really big, it is part of a huge JSON request. Workaround is to use an expression in Eclipse Debug Shell console and to output the substring of the whole value. Since you can see the partial value, inspect it and use the last few literals as the position to output the next chunk of the string. Repeat this approach until get what you need: </p>\n\n<pre><code>String result = new String(reallyBigByteArrayValue, \"UTF-8\");\nresult.substring(result.indexOf(\"some-unique-text\"));\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1620438,
      "reputation" : 15747,
      "user_id" : 1497139,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 68,
